> Our chef André has used the heady aromas of the East African spice route as inspiration for this warming curry. The mild spices add delicious flavour but not too much heat, making it suitable and tasty for the whole family!

Preheat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Place the @British Chicken Thighs{8} in a #bowl{}. Drizzle over a splash of @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Sprinkle in half of the @curry powder mix{1.5%tbsp} and then rub the spice into your chicken. Keep to one side.

Cut the @red onion{1} in half through the root, peel and then slice thinly into half moon shapes. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} and @ginger{1%inch piece} on the fine side of your #grater{} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and cut into 1cm slices.

Pop a #saucepan{} on medium heat and add a glug of @oil{}. Add your @red onion{1}(sliced) and @red pepper{1}(sliced) and cook for ~{5%minutes} or until soft. Add your @garlic clove{1}(grated), @ginger{1%inch piece}(grated), and remaining curry powder and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Add the @chopped tomatoes{1%400g can} and the @chicken stock pot{1/2}. Stir well and half fill the empty tomato tin with water, then add this to your pan. Bring your curry sauce to the boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer for ~{15%minutes}.

== Yellow Rice ==

Now to cook the rice. Put a #pot{} of @water{700%ml} on high heat and add the @cardamom pods{4}, the @ground turmeric{1/2%tsp} and a generous pinch of @salt{}. Bring to the boil and then add the @basmati rice{350%g}. Reduce the heat to low and cook your rice for ~{10%minutes} with the lid on. After 10 mins, remove the pot from the heat and leave your rice to finish cooking in its own steam, for ~{10%minutes} more. No peeking!

== Chicken ==

While your rice and curry sauce are cooking, get on with your chicken. Heat a #frying pan{} over medium-high heat (no oil). When the pan is hot, carefully lay your chicken in the pan and cook for ~{2%minutes} on each side. Make sure your chicken is browned all over before transferring to a #baking tray{}, then roasting in your oven for ~{12-15%minutes}.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

When cooked, remove your chicken from your oven and cover with #tinfoil{} to keep warm.

== Finishing ==

While everything cooks away, finish off your last few jobs. Remove the tops and bottoms from the @green beans{1}(trimmed). Chop your green beans into three pieces and add them to your curry sauce. They will need to cook for ~{10%minutes}. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}.

Fluff up your rice with a #fork{}. Add your parsley to your curry sauce, taste and add more @salt{} and @black pepper{} if necessary. Cut each chicken thigh in half lengthways.

Pop a generous amount of rice onto each plate, top with your chicken and curry sauce and enjoy!